	<Title>
		Exercise: Every minute counts!
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t have time for a full 60-minute workout? Don&apos;t sweat it. Divide and conquer. Shorter spurts of exercise, such as 10 minutes of walking spaced throughout the day, offer benefits too. Whether you&apos;re trying to lose weight or improve your cardiovascular fitness, the key is to get moving. Take the stairs, walk during your lunch break, and do household chores at a pace fast enough to get your heart pumping. It all adds up!&lt;/p&gt;
